.SH NAME
gnb-shell-init - Output shell functions for registered aliases and workflows


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgnb shell-init [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Output shell functions that can be eval'd to register aliases and workflows
as native shell commands.

.PP
Add this to your shell config:
  # bash/zsh
  eval "$(gnb shell-init)"

.PP
# fish
  gnb shell-init | source

.PP
Example:
  gnb shell-init
  gnb shell-init --shell fish


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for shell-init

.PP
\fB--shell\fP=""
	Shell type (bash, zsh, fish). Auto-detected if omitted


